{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review the child maintenance non-resident parents are required to pay by CMS",
        "additional_details": "We believe the existing amounts NRPs are required to pay in many cases too low, and that reforms are needed to more adequately support families.\r\n \r\nCurrently the NRP, if claiming benefits or with an income under \u00a3100 a week, pays only \u00a37 per week as a flat rate towards their child.\r\n \r\nWe want this rate, and the amount of child maintenance all NRPs are required to pay by the CMS, to be reviewed. We believe these should better reflect the average cost of bringing up a child in the UK.\r\n \r\nWe believe at present far too much pressure is being put on the resident parent to \u2018figure it out\u2019 financially.\r\n",
        "background": "We want a full review into the amount of child maintenance non-resident parents (NRPs) are required to pay by the CMS.",
